# Phase 35: Multi-Agent Deployment & Infrastructure Scaling

Following the "Cinematic Obsidian" overhaul, the Project Lead has ordered the deployment of 9 specialized agents across three critical domains to prepare for a public beta release.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The storage proposal represents a shift in architecture. Supabase Free Tier (1GB) is insufficient for 720p video hosting at scale. The agents propose integrating **Cloudflare R2** to maintain the <$5 budget while supporting HD media.

## Proposed Strategy (Agent Directives)

### Directive Alpha: UI Testing & Redesign (Agents 1-5)
- **Objective**: Rigorous QA and final visual polish of the "Cinematic Obsidian" theme.
- **Agent Roles**:
  - **Agents 1 & 2 (Visual QA)**: Cross-browser testing (Chrome, Safari, Firefox) for CSS variables, font rendering (Outfit/Bebas Neue), and glassmorphism fallbacks.
  - **Agents 3 & 4 (UX/Interaction)**: Auditing all hover states, transition timings, and mobile responsiveness. Ensuring the "BREACH PROTOCOL" auth flow is flawless.
  - **Agent 5 (Accessibility)**: Screen reader testing, ARIA label auditing, and contrast compliance (WCAG AA).
- **Execution**: Simulate browsing sessions; identify and patch any remaining CSS inline styles or layout shifts.

### Directive Beta: Ultra-Low Budget Deployment (Agents 6-7)
- **Objective**: Architect a production deployment strategy that costs $5 or less per month.
- **Agent Analysis**:
  - **Frontend Compute**: **Vercel Hobby Tier ($0)**. Next.js App Router and Edge Functions fit perfectly into the free limits.
  - **Database & Auth**: **Supabase Free Tier ($0)**. Supports 500k API requests and 50,000 active monthly auth users.
  - **Domain Registration**: **Namecheap/Cloudflare ($5/year)**. 
- **Execution**: Finalize Vercel configuration (`next.config.js`) and ensure Supabase API keys are securely vaulted. Total monthly operational cost: **$0.00**.

### Directive Gamma: 720p Video & Audio Storage (Agents 8-9)
- **Objective**: Design a storage architecture capable of handling 720p HD video and high-quality audio uploads without exceeding budget.
- **Agent Analysis**:
  - **Current Limitation**: Supabase Free Tier limits storage to 1GB. A single 10-minute 720p web-optimized MP4 is ~150MB. This allows for only ~6 videos before hitting the cap.
  - **Proposed Solution**: **Cloudflare R2**. 
    - *Cost*: 10GB/month FREE. Zero egress fees (crucial for video playback).
    - *Integration*: Replace Supabase Storage with AWS S3 SDK connecting to Cloudflare R2 for video uploads.
  - **Streaming Strategy**: Store compressed MP4s (H.264) directly on R2. Use `<video>` HTML5 tags to stream directly from Cloudflare's global CDN for buffer-free 720p playback.
- **Execution**: Agents will draft the R2 integration code and update the upload mechanisms in the application.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Integration tests simulating a 720p large file upload to ensure timeout/chunking logic holds up.

### Manual Verification
- Project Lead reviews the final Vercel deployment and validates playback performance of a 720p test asset.
